				 																THE BOOK				 																																	(Yashodabai  Joshi) Simply and lucidly told, its the tale of Sir Moropant  and Lady Yashodabai Joshi. The first-person account, dictated  to her third daughter on her deathbed and translated into  English by her grandson Vijay Kumar Bhide, covers some of  the most important incidents in the nations history, through  the lives of two extraordinary people, from 1868 to 1948  THE SHOW				 																																	(Tollygunge  Club, Sunday, 11.30 am) Tollygunge Clubs annual Vintage Car  display will showcase about 30 cars, some of them over 70  years old, and will be on till 1.30 pm  THE CD				 																																	(Fairport  Convention) This was the second LP of the group recorded in  1968 and was characterised by the same medley of folk, blues,  cajun, medieval and country that marked their first album.  The outfits favourite songwriters Bob Dylan and Joni Mitchell  were also represented  THE FESTIVAL				 																																	(Saturday  amp; Sunday at C3, Lee Residency) The new supermarket at  the Lee Road-Elgin Road junction lays out a mouth-watering  spread of traditional Bengali sweets by Balarams 

